  "name": "Fried Daing na Bangus with Garlic Fried Rice, Fried Egg, and Pickled Papaya (Daing Silog)",
  "recipe_type": null,
  "brief_description": "Fried Daing na Bangus with Garlic Fried Rice, Fried Egg, and Pickled Papaya or simply Daing Silog is a type of meal wherein fish is paired with rice and egg",
  "cuisine": null,
  "instructions": [
    {
      "position": 1,
      "text": "Prepare daing na bangus according to the instructions on the recipe link above. Set aside."
    },
    {
      "position": 2,
      "text": "Prepare sinangag (garlic fried rice). See link above for the recipe. Set Aside"
    },
    {
      "position": 3,
      "text": "Heat oil in a pan. Once the oil gets hot, fry the eggs. You can make it sunny side-up, over easy, or basted. Get more details here"
    },
    {
      "position": 4,
      "text": "Arrange the fried daing na bangus, sinangag, and fried egg on individual plates. Serve with papaya atchara and spicy vinegar. Sprinkle some chopped scallions on top."
    },
    {
      "position": 5,
      "text": "Share and enjoy"
    }
  ],
